name: black industrial can with chain
description: A great vintage black industrial can with original chain. Probably a gas or oil can or some sort. Approximately 8" tall. Original patina.

name: vintage green part bins - size small
description: Fresh from a workshop in Bethlehem, PA, this stash of green painted metal part bins. Two sizes to choose from: this one is the SMALL: approximately 2" wide and 6" deep. Great for desk storage! As found.

name: vintage green part bins - size large
description: Fresh from a workshop in Bethlehem, PA, this stash of green painted metal part bins. Two sizes to choose from: this one is the LARGE: approximately 4" wide and 6" deep. Great for desk storage! As found.

name: antique brass German Shepard figure
description: An estate find: beautiful detailed brass German Shepard. Approximately 6" long and 3.5" tall at the head.

name: antique French binoculars with original case and leather strap!
description: Not only are these in amazing shape, but they have travelled some 80+ years with their original case and neck strap! Just beautiful.

name: antique "Good Luck" money clip with engraving
description: Found a drawer full of antique money clips at an estate sale! This one is silver with an engraved message on the back. Sweet!

name: vintage birdhouse no. 3
description: One of a collection of 12 vintage birdhouses found at an estate in California. This one is 10" high and 10" wide. As found. It even has a little back door to check on the nests!

name: vintage movie theatre marquee letters
description: A whole bunch of vintage movie theatre marquee letters. Each is 10" tall. Original patina. Made from some sort of very heavy plastic!

name: antique 1944 oil on linen painting
description: A vivid, beautiful oil painting of a man in a suit. The background colors and incredible. Signed in the upper right corner and dated 1944. In what appears to be the original frame. As found. Approximately 34" tall x 26" wide.

name: vintage wooden tennis rackets
description: Smashing! Four vintage wooden tennis rackets. Original strings, emblems and leather tipped handles. As found and aged to perfection.

name: vintage original art on board - female figure with book
description: An original vintage art piece on board. No signature. Image approximately 12" tall x 9" wide. Board is 20" tall x 15" wide.

name: enamelware camp coffee pot No. 2
description: Vintage enamelware camp coffee pot. As found, beautiful shape with one tiny rust spot on the outside bottom. Original handle, hinges and even a little pouring support handle! Approximately 11" tall.

name: vintage Pendleton blanket with original black label
description: Completely original with little to no wear at all! No holes, no damage. Some slight wear to the binding, but totally intact. One of two we found by chance on a hunting trip in the Pacific Northwest. Original black label intact!

name: vintage pewter bud vase
description: Local estate find. A pewter bud vase from Norway. Stamped on the bottom, and the finish is as found. Approximately 6" tall.

name: 10" vintage enamel light shades
description: 10" vintage enamel shade covers. As found, some wear and spots from being outside for half a century!

name: set of vintage wooden hat molds
description: A vintage set of wooden hat molds. Very sculptural and in as found condition. Some are marked on top with the hat size. This set is FOUR molds.

name: vintage brass horse trophy
description: As found trophy topper. Brass with patina and age spots. Approximately 9" wide and 7" tall.

name: vintage WW1 compass
description: Stamped, vintage WW1 compass. Marked "ENG DEPT 1918 USA". Works.

name: vintage WWII canteen
description: amazing condition on this vintage WWII canteen. approximately 8" tall. Felt is completely intact.

name: Native American rug No. 23
description: A vintage woven rug. Approximately 2' x 4'.  No major holes or issues. In amazing shape.

name: delicate vintage ring box
description: One of two from an estate. German made. Not sure of the material, but looks like copper or brass over nickel. This one is tiny, the size of just one ring, and has a beautiful purple stone (or glass) on top. Perhaps not one of a kind, but certainly one of the only one of it's kind that we have come across. As found.

name: vintage amber apothecary bottles
description: Beautiful amber bottles. No lids. Price is per bottle. Approximately 9" tall.

name: vintage horse shoe
description: Vintage horse shoe. As found. Rusty and well used. Approximately 6" tall.

name: vintage leather belt with brass buckle
description: A vintage, aged, worn leather belt with brass buckle and rivets. Can be worn or used as a display piece, a photo prop, etc. As found.

name: vintage Danish flag
description: A beautiful vintage Danish flag. Approximately 2' x 3'. Was flown, so some slight wear, consistent with age. Appears to be cotton/linen.

name: set of small milk glass jars
description: A vintage set of three white milk glass jars. Original lids. 2.5" tall. Price is for the set.

name: antique Art Deco lamp
description: Worn to perfection, this is an Art Deco table lamp from a local estate. Female form. Completely original patina. Cord and plug have been replaced and updated, using period appropriate braided cloth cord. 14" tall.

name: vintage hose nozzle No. 3
description: a solid brass vintage hose nozzle. great sculptural piece. Approximately 4" tall.

name: vintage wooden mallets
description: Price is per mallet, there are two available.

name: small vintage crazed crock
description: A small and fantastically crazed crock. Marked on bottom. Approximately 3" tall and 3.5" wide.

name: set of four vintage white prep bowls
description: Set of four white bowls. Each is the same size. One has a small chip. Each is marked "Hall 352" on the bottom. Approximately 3" tall. Price is for the set.

name: antique hand held mirror with wood handle No. 8
description: A dark wood hand held mirror. Beveled glass. Approximately 8" tall. In as found condition, the beautiful patina left untouched.

name: vintage wooden box No. 3
description: A beautiful estate find with a well worn patina. Beautiful original brass drawer pull. One drawer and opens from the top as well.

name: vintage white mixing bowl
description: A simple white vintage mixing bowl. No cracks or chips. Approximately 8" across.

name: industrial factory cart with casters
description: So many uses for these amazing industrial carts! Shown are a few examples: as a kitchen display piece for vintage yellow ware; as a bedroom side table with lamp and books, or as a bar! Would also work as a store display for denim or goods, books, etc. Cart is approximately 38" wide and 62" tall, with a handle on either the right or the left. Each piece has a unique patina, so we would be happy to show you what we have and you can pick the one you want! We apologize, but due to the weight of these carts, we only offer local pick up here in Southern California. There is no shipping option.

name: antique US Army wool blanket
description: In incredible shape, no holes or tears of any kind. Big enough to fit a double bed.

name: vintage fishing lures in worn leather case
description: Oh! An amazing set of vintage fishing lures, still in their original leather case. Zipper works. Some lures from France, others American. All lures are included in the price. Perfect vintage provision for the modern man!

name: vintage Navajo rug No. 11
description: Our hearts always skip a beat when we find these Navajo rugs. Beautiful pattern and a deep red make this one a real eye catcher. One small stain, not very noticeable. One corner missing about 1" of weaving. Email for additional pics and details.

name: pair of vintage polychromed lamps
description: Pair of 1920's polychromed lamps. Approximately 14" tall. Candle wraps are original and intact. Just in beautiful shape and a great addition to any early 1920's-30's interior. Price is for the pair.

name: vintage McCoy pottery
description: A small white McCoy planter. Amazing crazing on this one, with some age related discoloration. No chips or cracks. Approximately 6" tall.

name: vintage woven rug No. 214
description: A colorful flat weave vintage rug. Uncertain origin. Has one small area where the weave is coming apart. Approximate size 36" long x 24" wide.

name: British "Camp" Coffee with Chickory Tin
description: Old British coffee tin. Approximately 12" tall. Includes original lid. Marked "England" on the bottom, although the coffee company is based in Glasgow.

name: vintage Italian belt buckle
description: A vintage find form Italy. Sweet little star buckle. Could be used for a belt as intended, or refashioned as an awesome scarf tie. Metal of some sort, but not heavy. Marked on back.

name: Neil Jakobe Native American painting
description: An estate find by Neil Jakobe, a local California artist and illustrator at McDonnell Douglas. His work has only recently hit the market, and two of his works were just sold at auction. This one is an unfinished work with a Native American scene. Great colors. Approximately 17" tall x 20" wide.

name: two vintage cutting boards
description: Small, well worn cutting boards. Use or display...they are perfect for both! Approximately 5" wide x 7" long. Price is for the set.

name: vintage kilim rug
description: A beautiful vintage kilim rug. Approximately 9.9' x 12'. In excellent condition.

name: St Theresa statue
description: A small, delicate, beautifully painted statue of St Theresa. Approximately 5" tall.

name: vintage desert water carrier
description: Vintage water carrier  circa 1930's San Francisco. A beautiful piece of California history.

name: leather suitcase
description: A very well travelled vintage suitcase. As found, with heavy (and amazing!) wear throughout. Opens. Approximately 20" wide.

name: vintage copper ship lamp
description: A beautiful early copper ship lamp with just the right amount of patina.
